The paper deals with the construction of codes and their weight distributions, which are topics in information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of character sums suggests a connection to algebraic coding theory (cs.DM). The codes are also quasi-cyclic, which is a topic in coding theory (cs.CC). Finally, the application to secret sharing schemes suggests a connection to cybersecurity (cs.CY).
